text: Thomas Moriarty (1812, Dingle - 1894, Tralee) was a clergyman in the Church of Ireland"A New History of Ireland" Moody,T.W; Martin,F.X; Byrne,F.J;Cosgrove,A: Oxford, OUP, 1976 during the nineteenth century."Handbook of British Chronology" By Fryde, E. B;. Greenway, D.E;Porter, S; Roy, I: Cambridge, CUP, 1996 , 9780521563505 Moriarty was educated at Trinity College, Dublin.Alumni Dublinenses : a register of the students, graduates, professors and provosts of Trinity College in the University of Dublin (1593-1860), Burtchaell,G.D/Sadlier,T.U 598: Dublin, Alex Thom and Co, 1935 Moriarty was ordained in 1837. He served curacies at Kingscourt and Ventry; and incumbencies at Dunquin, Kildrum, Tralee, Ballynacourty and Drishane. He was Treasurer of Ardfert Cathedral from 1873 to 1879; and Dean of Ardfert from 1879 to 1894."The Church of Ireland in County Kerry" Murphy, J.A. p243: Cork, Lulu, 2016 He died on 26 April 1894.THE CHURCH OF IRELAND.Belfast News-Letter (Belfast, Ireland), Monday, May 7, 1894; Issue 24599 ==References== Category:Deans of Ardfert Category:Alumni of Trinity College Dublin Category:1812 births Category:1894 deaths Category:People from Dingle
